er, and only one parameter can\nbe estimated with the other two being either fixed or marginalized. We use the\nensemble averaging method to estimate the RGW spectrum from the un-integrated\noutput signals. We also adopt a correlation of un-integrated signals to\nestimate the spectrum and three parameters of RGW in a Bayesian approach. For\nall methods, we provide simulations to illustrate their feasibility.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Aug 2018 01:59:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Jan 2019 11:23:30 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 14 Feb 2019 11:20:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2019 14:49:51 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 3 Mar 2019 10:34:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-05"}
