 optical and thermal profiles, and the growth of large particles in the\nmidplane can make a massive disk optically thick at millimeter wavelengths,\nmaking it difficult to calculate the surface density of dust available for\nplanet formation in the inner disk. Also, for an initially massive disk, grain\nsettling and growth can produce a drop in the Toomre Q parameter, driving the\ndisk to $Q < 1.4$ and possibly triggering spiral instabilities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Aug 2018 04:23:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-27"}
